oy Way]]'') (1994)\n*''[[Waking the Dead (album)|Waking the Dead]]'' \u2013 [[L.A. Guns]] (2002)\n*''[[22nd Century Lifestyle]]'' \u2013 [[pre)Thing]] (2004)\n*''[[Rips the Covers Off]]'' \u2013 [[L.A. Guns]] (2004)\n*''Shake The Hand That Shook The World'' \u2013 Pepper's Ghost (2005)\n*''Stone in the Sand'' \u2013 Euphoraphonic (2005)\n*''[[Tales from the Strip]]'' \u2013 [[L.A. Guns]] (2005)\n*''[[IV (Godsmack album)|IV]]'' \u2013 [[Godsmack]] (2006)\n*''[[The Undercover Sessions]]'' \u2013 [[Ill Ni\u00f1o]] (2006)\n*''Radio Romeo'' \u2013 [[Radio Romeo]] (2007)\n*''[[Chickenfoot]]'' \u2013 [[Chickenfoot]] (2009)<ref>{{cite web|author=Joel Selvin |url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2009/05/08/PKTA17AQQJ.DTL |title=Guitarist Satriani joins Hagar for Chickenfoot fun |publisher=SFGate |date=10 May 2009 |accessdate=8 April 2013}}</ref>\n*''[[Bingo! (Steve Miller Band album)|Bingo!]]'' \u2013 [[Steve Miller Band]] (2010)\n* [[Willie Basse]]  *\"Break Away\", [23][24] Rock's Cool Music Publishing, New Empire Media, Inc. (2010) Andy Johns Co-Producer, Engineer https://itun.es/us/Yu2xx{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n*''[[Up Close (Eric Johnson album)|Up Close]]'' \u2013 [[Eric Johnson (guitarist, born 1954)|Eric Johnson]] (2010)\n*''Double Four Time'' \u2013 The Swayback (2012)\n*''Hollywood Forever'' \u2013 [[L.A. Guns]] (2012)\n*''Laugh Until I Die'' \u2013 [[Sabyrtooth]] (2014/TBA)\n*''Get Your Rock On'' \u2013 X-Drive (2014)\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Albums engineered===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n*''[[Stand Up (Jethro Tull album)|Stand Up]]'' \u2013 [[Jethro Tull (band)|Jethro Tull]] (1969)\n*''[[Town and Country (album)|Town and Country]]'' \u2013 [[Humble Pie]] (1969)\n*''[[Disposable (album)|Disposable]]'' \u2013 [[The Deviants (band)|The Deviants]] (1968)\n*''[[Spooky Two]]'' \u2013 [[Spooky Tooth]] (1969)\n*''[[Renaissance (Renaissance album)|Renaissance]]'' \u2013 [[Renaissance (band)|Renaissance]] (1969)\n*'